cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with face pose estimation from 2D images. The use of deep learning frameworks and multi-modal data also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Additionally, the use of multi-modal data and mapping relationships could also suggest that it belongs to the Multimedia (cs.MM) category. Finally, the use of manifold regularization and multi-task learning could suggest that it belongs to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category.
